1
00:00:02.439 --> 00:00:06.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 51247.5.</i>

2
00:00:06.778 --> 00:00:09.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's been a week since</i>
<i>our return to Deep Space 9,</i>

3
00:00:09.437 --> 00:00:11.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but the mood</i>
<i>of celebration continues.</i>

4
00:00:11.655 --> 00:00:13.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We're still at war,</i>
<i>and the station's</i>

5
00:00:13.577 --> 00:00:15.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>been designated headquarters</i>
<i>for the Ninth Fleet.</i>

6
00:00:16.015 --> 00:00:17.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That, plus</i>
<i>our strategic position</i>

7
00:00:17.796 --> 00:00:19.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>guarding the wormhole,</i>
<i>makes DS9</i>

8
00:00:19.794 --> 00:00:21.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>one of the most</i>
<i>tempting targets</i>

9
00:00:21.452 --> 00:00:22.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>in the entire quadrant.</i>

10
00:00:23.152 --> 00:00:26.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But for now, at least,</i>
<i>the war seems very far away.</i>

11
00:00:33.069 --> 00:00:34.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Morning.
-Good morning.

12
00:00:34.548 --> 00:00:35.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning.

13
00:00:35.788 --> 00:00:37.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Morning, Major.

14
00:00:37.108 --> 00:00:39.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning, Captain.

15
00:00:39.128 --> 00:00:40.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
how much I missed

16
00:00:40.368 --> 00:00:41.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
hearing you say that?

17
00:00:41.689 --> 00:00:43.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how much
I hated saying

18
00:00:43.590 --> 00:00:44.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Good morning, Dukat"?

19
00:00:44.436 --> 00:00:45.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can imagine.

20
00:00:46.152 --> 00:00:46.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's on the agenda?

21
00:00:47.185 --> 00:00:49.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, USS <i>Potemkin</i>
has completed her repairs

22
00:00:49.947 --> 00:00:51.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and is rejoining the fleet
later today.

23
00:00:51.987 --> 00:00:53.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Exeter, Sutherland</i>
and <i>Agaki</i>

24
00:00:53.964 --> 00:00:55.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have submitted
resupply requests

25
00:00:55.665 --> 00:00:57.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and there are
about 1,000 messages

26
00:00:57.615 --> 00:00:58.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
from Starfleet Command

27
00:00:59.014 --> 00:01:00.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
awaiting your "eyes-only"
attention.

28
00:01:00.894 --> 00:01:02.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else?

29
00:01:02.301 --> 00:01:04.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
General Martok is waiting
in your office.

30
00:01:04.122 --> 00:01:05.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I'll start
with the General.

31
00:01:05.921 --> 00:01:07.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you would.

32
00:01:09.387 --> 00:01:11.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have I mentioned
that it's good to be home?

33
00:01:13.306 --> 00:01:15.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Once or twice.

34
00:01:17.288 --> 00:01:18.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

35
00:01:22.755 --> 00:01:24.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You knew about this,
didn't you?

36
00:01:24.514 --> 00:01:26.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I had a pretty good idea.

37
00:01:26.695 --> 00:01:28.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you did nothing to stop it.

38
00:01:30.412 --> 00:01:31.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

39
00:01:31.053 --> 00:01:33.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In fact, I recommended you
for the position myself.

40
00:01:33.692 --> 00:01:35.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to offer
my congratulations

41
00:01:35.752 --> 00:01:37.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the new
Supreme Commander

42
00:01:37.431 --> 00:01:38.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the Ninth Fleet.

43
00:01:40.991 --> 00:01:42.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
how much paperwork

44
00:01:42.609 --> 00:01:44.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a Supreme Commander
has to do?

45
00:01:44.809 --> 00:01:45.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

46
00:01:45.849 --> 00:01:47.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>growls </i>)

47
00:01:47.888 --> 00:01:49.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I arrange quarters
for you on the station?

48
00:01:49.728 --> 00:01:53.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I'll keep my flag
aboard the <i>Rotarran.</i>

49
00:01:53.167 --> 00:01:56.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It may be cramped but at least I'll feel
like I'm still in the war.

50
00:01:56.645 --> 00:01:59.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By the way, I'd like Worf
to continue functioning

51
00:01:59.605 --> 00:02:01.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as my principal
Intelligence Officer.

52
00:02:01.324 --> 00:02:02.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't see any problem
with that.

53
00:02:03.283 --> 00:02:06.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's the only officer I know
who can never get enough work.

54
00:02:06.576 --> 00:02:08.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>cackles </i>)

55
00:02:08.288 --> 00:02:09.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, at least if he's busy

56
00:02:09.722 --> 00:02:12.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he'll stop going on
about this wedding of his.

57
00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:16.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, there were times
aboard the <i>Rotarran</i>

58
00:02:16.948 --> 00:02:17.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he nearly drove me mad.

59
00:02:17.924 --> 00:02:20.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until his son arrived,
it was all he could talk about.

60
00:02:21.037 --> 00:02:23.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then Alexander became
all he could talk about.

61
00:02:23.877 --> 00:02:27.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The man is nothing
if not single-minded.

62
00:02:27.616 --> 00:02:29.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't met Worf's son yet.

63
00:02:29.157 --> 00:02:29.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's he like?

64
00:02:31.117 --> 00:02:32.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's a fine boy...

65
00:02:32.955 --> 00:02:35.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dedicated, eager.

66
00:02:35.039 --> 00:02:36.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the heart
of his father

67
00:02:38.113 --> 00:02:40.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but he's not the best
soldier I've ever seen.

68
00:02:41.852 --> 00:02:44.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But when he ordered me
to bring the system back online,

69
00:02:44.133 --> 00:02:45.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought he was still talking

70
00:02:45.183 --> 00:02:46.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the hydro-static
system, so...

71
00:02:47.510 --> 00:02:48.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You didn't
engage the pumps

72
00:02:48.969 --> 00:02:50.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while the check valves
were open.

73
00:02:50.210 --> 00:02:51.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He did.

74
00:02:51.889 --> 00:02:53.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I flooded
the entire deck

75
00:02:53.350 --> 00:02:54.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with super-heated
hydraulic fluid.

76
00:02:55.587 --> 00:02:57.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It took me three days
to clean it up

77
00:02:57.847 --> 00:03:01.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but, I swear, it still smells
like burnt dog hair in there.

78
00:03:01.009 --> 00:03:03.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh! Remind me to keep you away
from the <i>Defiant. </i>You're a menace.

79
00:03:03.885 --> 00:03:06.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The <i>Rotarran's </i>crew actually thinks of me
as a good luck charm.

80
00:03:06.617 --> 00:03:10.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, the more mistakes
<i>I </i>make, the safer <i>they </i>feel.

81
00:03:11.762 --> 00:03:13.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope the <i>Ya'Vang's crew</i>
feels the same way.

82
00:03:14.162 --> 00:03:15.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The <i>Ya'Vang?</i>

83
00:03:17.202 --> 00:03:18.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I got new orders this morning.

84
00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The battle cruiser <i>Ya'Vang</i>
took heavy losses

85
00:03:21.421 --> 00:03:22.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in their last engagement

86
00:03:22.541 --> 00:03:25.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so most of the <i>Rotarran's crew</i>
are being transferred there

87
00:03:25.672 --> 00:03:27.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
at the end of the week,
including me.

88
00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:32.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, more bloodwine?

89
00:03:32.510 --> 00:03:33.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not?

90
00:03:33.709 --> 00:03:36.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Not for me.

91
00:03:37.482 --> 00:03:38.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Handsome young man.

92
00:03:39.067 --> 00:03:40.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He must get his looks
from his mother's side.

93
00:03:41.214 --> 00:03:42.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you want?

94
00:03:43.153 --> 00:03:45.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you had a chance
to reconsider my offer?

95
00:03:46.612 --> 00:03:48.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are not getting
married in this bar.

96
00:03:48.691 --> 00:03:51.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ceremony will take place
on the Klingon homeworld

97
00:03:51.148 --> 00:03:51.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
after the war.

98
00:03:53.313 --> 00:03:55.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, let's do it here,
this week

99
00:03:55.473 --> 00:03:56.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before Alexander leaves.

100
00:03:56.792 --> 00:03:58.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Perfect.

101
00:03:58.032 --> 00:03:59.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll handle
all the arrangements.

102
00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:01.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait. I thought
we had agreed.

103
00:04:02.128 --> 00:04:04.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We did, but I would hate
for Alexander

104
00:04:04.287 --> 00:04:05.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to miss
his father's wedding.

105
00:04:05.566 --> 00:04:07.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It would mean so much to him.

106
00:04:08.685 --> 00:04:11.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And besides,
it may be a long time

107
00:04:11.827 --> 00:04:13.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before you see him again.

108
00:04:19.265 --> 00:04:21.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's going on?

109
00:04:24.267 --> 00:04:25.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our wedding plans
have changed.

110
00:04:26.281 --> 00:04:28.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are getting married here
on Deep Space 9

111
00:04:29.419 --> 00:04:31.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I would like you
to be my <i>Tawi'Yan.</i>

112
00:04:35.738 --> 00:04:37.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Sword-bearer."

113
00:04:37.867 --> 00:04:39.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's sort of like
a best man.

114
00:04:40.346 --> 00:04:42.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

115
00:04:42.346 --> 00:04:42.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

116
00:04:43.626 --> 00:04:44.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's great!

117
00:04:44.585 --> 00:04:46.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>yelping </i>)

118
00:04:48.344 --> 00:04:50.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll put that
on your tab.

119
00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:47.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
It doesn't leave much time

120
00:06:47.239 --> 00:06:48.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make
all the arrangements

121
00:06:48.389 --> 00:06:50.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but fortunately, there isn't
that much left to do.

122
00:06:50.859 --> 00:06:52.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf's been planning
the ceremony

123
00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:53.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for the last three months.

124
00:06:54.196 --> 00:06:55.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
He has everything
figured out

125
00:06:55.617 --> 00:06:57.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
right down
to the color of my shoes.

126
00:06:57.656 --> 00:07:00.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
No offense, Jadzia,
but it seems like this wedding's

127
00:07:00.415 --> 00:07:01.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
all about what Worf wants.

128
00:07:02.309 --> 00:07:04.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Uh, Habitat Ring,
Section 51 Gamma.

129
00:07:04.694 --> 00:07:06.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What about you?

130
00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:09.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A traditional Klingon wedding
with all the trimmings

131
00:07:09.413 --> 00:07:12.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
is something Worf's
been thinking about since he was a boy.

132
00:07:12.471 --> 00:07:14.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It probably has something
to do with being raised

133
00:07:14.292 --> 00:07:15.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
by human parents.

134
00:07:15.988 --> 00:07:18.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
In any case, when it comes
to Klingon tradition,

135
00:07:18.410 --> 00:07:19.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf is very sentimental.

136
00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:20.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf?

137
00:07:21.628 --> 00:07:22.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
All men are sentimental.

138
00:07:23.667 --> 00:07:27.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They just cover it up with
scowls and clenched jaws.

139
00:07:27.146 --> 00:07:31.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
There are times when Worf
literally gets misty-eyed

140
00:07:31.585 --> 00:07:33.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
talking about
Klingon rituals.

141
00:07:35.036 --> 00:07:36.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
So, uh, that's
why you're letting him

142
00:07:36.664 --> 00:07:37.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
make the plans
for the wedding?

143
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:39.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mostly, but
the truth is

144
00:07:39.613 --> 00:07:40.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've already
been through five

145
00:07:40.978 --> 00:07:41.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Trill ceremonies--

146
00:07:42.327 --> 00:07:43.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
three as a bride,
two as a groom,

147
00:07:44.001 --> 00:07:45.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and I'm a little bored with it.

148
00:07:45.101 --> 00:07:46.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Is it my imagination

149
00:07:46.338 --> 00:07:47.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
or did Odo just
try and avoid us?

150
00:07:47.960 --> 00:07:48.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I didn't notice.

151
00:07:49.879 --> 00:07:50.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

152
00:07:51.259 --> 00:07:52.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We've been avoiding
each other

153
00:07:52.440 --> 00:07:54.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
ever since the Dominion
left the station.

154
00:07:54.758 --> 00:07:56.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I think we're both
afraid of talking

155
00:07:56.139 --> 00:07:57.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
about what happened
during the occupation.

156
00:07:58.924 --> 00:07:59.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What do you mean?

157
00:08:01.136 --> 00:08:03.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, to tell you the truth,

158
00:08:03.496 --> 00:08:06.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
it's nothing I want to talk
about right now either.

159
00:08:08.973 --> 00:08:09.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Thank you for coming.

160
00:08:10.526 --> 00:08:11.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
As you probably know by now,

161
00:08:13.048 --> 00:08:14.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia and I will be married
here on the station in six days.

162
00:08:15.012 --> 00:08:16.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's nothing
more romantic

163
00:08:16.091 --> 00:08:18.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than a wedding on
DS9 in springtime.

164
00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When the neutrinos
are in bloom.

165
00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:23.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By tradition,
the Klingon man spends

166
00:08:23.652 --> 00:08:24.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the four nights
before his wedding

167
00:08:25.089 --> 00:08:26.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on a mental
and spiritual journey.

168
00:08:27.048 --> 00:08:29.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is called <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
"The Path of Clarity"

169
00:08:30.368 --> 00:08:33.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and </i>he is accompanied
by his closest male friends.

170
00:08:34.045 --> 00:08:36.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You cannot imagine
the experience that awaits us--

171
00:08:36.745 --> 00:08:40.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
four long nights filled
with song and fellowship.

172
00:08:41.344 --> 00:08:43.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A time of unbridled pleasures.

173
00:08:43.663 --> 00:08:46.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are we talking
about a bachelor party here?

174
00:08:46.803 --> 00:08:48.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a similar ritual.

175
00:08:49.123 --> 00:08:50.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds good to me.

176
00:08:51.084 --> 00:08:52.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

177
00:08:52.162 --> 00:08:54.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Count me in.

178
00:08:54.476 --> 00:08:55.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We will meet
in the holosuite

179
00:08:55.209 --> 00:08:56.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
tomorrow night
at 2100 hours.

180
00:08:56.700 --> 00:08:58.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK: I advise you all
to get plenty of rest.

181
00:08:58.740 --> 00:09:00.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Four nights
at a Klingon bachelor party.

182
00:09:00.979 --> 00:09:02.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just think of
the possibilities.

183
00:09:02.498 --> 00:09:03.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank God
Keiko's not here.

184
00:09:03.597 --> 00:09:04.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder what Dax
will be doing

185
00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:06.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while we're traveling
down <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

186
00:09:06.857 --> 00:09:08.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She will be taking
a different journey...

187
00:09:09.215 --> 00:09:11.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my wife.

188
00:09:12.494 --> 00:09:13.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your wife?

189
00:09:18.893 --> 00:09:20.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By marrying Worf,

190
00:09:20.813 --> 00:09:22.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax will be joining
the House of Martok.

191
00:09:22.813 --> 00:09:23.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since the mistress
of a great House

192
00:09:23.872 --> 00:09:25.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
must approve all marriages,

193
00:09:25.552 --> 00:09:26.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella will spend
the next four days

194
00:09:26.890 --> 00:09:28.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
evaluating Jadzia.

195
00:09:36.407 --> 00:09:38.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My lady.

196
00:09:38.167 --> 00:09:40.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've put on weight...

197
00:09:40.886 --> 00:09:43.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and your hair is going gray.

198
00:09:44.625 --> 00:09:48.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My deterioration
is proceeding apace.

199
00:09:49.444 --> 00:09:51.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you would be
in your grave by now.

200
00:09:52.402 --> 00:09:53.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckling </i>)

201
00:09:53.362 --> 00:09:54.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I shall endeavor to die--

202
00:09:54.822 --> 00:09:56.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this year, if possible.

203
00:09:56.761 --> 00:09:59.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to present
Captain Benjamin Sisko,

204
00:09:59.520 --> 00:10:01.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander of Deep Space 9.

205
00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:03.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain, may I present

206
00:10:03.499 --> 00:10:06.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the mistress of the House
of Martok, my wife

207
00:10:06.080 --> 00:10:07.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the mother
of my children...

208
00:10:07.878 --> 00:10:10.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sirella, daughter of Linkasa.

209
00:10:10.837 --> 00:10:12.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Welcome to
Deep Space 9.

210
00:10:13.436 --> 00:10:15.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Captain.

211
00:10:15.556 --> 00:10:16.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is she?

212
00:10:16.988 --> 00:10:18.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia's quarters
are in the Habitat Ring,

213
00:10:18.817 --> 00:10:20.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Section... 25 Alpha.

214
00:10:21.654 --> 00:10:22.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shall I escort you?

215
00:10:23.234 --> 00:10:24.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's quite far away.

216
00:10:24.293 --> 00:10:25.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll find my way.

217
00:10:29.211 --> 00:10:30.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you'll excuse me.

218
00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:37.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Magnificent, isn't she?

219
00:10:45.946 --> 00:10:48.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are those real
<i>var'Hama </i>candles?

220
00:10:48.966 --> 00:10:50.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, Worf,
I traveled to Kronos.

221
00:10:50.785 --> 00:10:53.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I captured three <i>targs</i>
in the Hamar mountains,

222
00:10:53.704 --> 00:10:55.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
made the ritual
sacrifice at dawn,

223
00:10:55.564 --> 00:10:57.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
came back
to the station,

224
00:10:57.563 --> 00:10:59.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
asked Quark to boil their
shoulders into tallow.

225
00:10:59.602 --> 00:11:02.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then, I spent two days
molding them into candles

226
00:11:02.774 --> 00:11:03.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my own hands.

227
00:11:04.501 --> 00:11:05.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was just asking.

228
00:11:06.161 --> 00:11:08.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were
criticizing <i>again.</i>

229
00:11:09.219 --> 00:11:11.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Relax. She's not
going to reject

230
00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:12.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a prospective daughter

231
00:11:12.941 --> 00:11:14.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because the
<i>var'Hama </i>candles

232
00:11:14.619 --> 00:11:16.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in her welcoming
display were replicated.

233
00:11:16.138 --> 00:11:17.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

234
00:11:17.297 --> 00:11:17.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come in.

235
00:11:23.935 --> 00:11:26.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Tug son bosh mok</i>
<i>A'Beh, Sirella koH.</i>

236
00:11:26.894 --> 00:11:28.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>E'Gagh vet moh.</i>

237
00:11:29.254 --> 00:11:31.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is <i>he </i>doing here?

238
00:11:31.493 --> 00:11:33.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I meant no disrespect.

239
00:11:34.095 --> 00:11:34.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then leave.

240
00:11:42.449 --> 00:11:45.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your worthiness to join
our House will now be judged

241
00:11:46.108 --> 00:11:48.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
according to the traditions
of my family.

242
00:11:48.727 --> 00:11:49.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am prepared, my lady.

243
00:11:50.248 --> 00:11:51.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I doubt that.

244
00:11:51.626 --> 00:11:55.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman would find it
difficult to gain my favor.

245
00:11:55.866 --> 00:11:57.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For...an <i>alien,</i>

246
00:11:58.264 --> 00:12:00.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it will most likely
be impossible.

247
00:12:00.984 --> 00:12:02.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like a challenge.

248
00:12:02.683 --> 00:12:05.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I will not have my authority
challenged by you.

249
00:12:06.982 --> 00:12:08.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I meant.

250
00:12:08.302 --> 00:12:11.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you cannot say what you mean,
say nothing at all.

251
00:12:12.961 --> 00:12:15.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The evaluation
will begin tomorrow morning.

252
00:12:15.699 --> 00:12:19.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have the traditional meal
prepared before I arrive.

253
00:12:21.078 --> 00:12:22.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And in the future,

254
00:12:22.616 --> 00:12:26.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you cannot trouble yourself
to make real <i>var'Hama </i>candles,

255
00:12:27.016 --> 00:12:29.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
try not to use
such obvious fakes.

256
00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:47.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You never told me that your wife
was opposed to this marriage.

257
00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:50.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella is a woman
of strong convictions.

258
00:12:50.150 --> 00:12:51.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She believes
that by bringing aliens

259
00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:54.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
into our families,
we risk losing our identity

260
00:12:54.491 --> 00:12:55.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as Klingons.

261
00:12:55.125 --> 00:12:57.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That is a prejudiced,
xenophobic view.

262
00:12:57.587 --> 00:12:59.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We <i>are </i>Klingons, Worf.

263
00:12:59.586 --> 00:13:03.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We don't <i>embrace </i>other cultures.
We <i>conquer </i>them.

264
00:13:03.386 --> 00:13:06.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If someone wishes to join us,
they must honor our traditions

265
00:13:06.845 --> 00:13:08.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and prove themselves worthy

266
00:13:08.224 --> 00:13:10.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of wearing the crest
of a Great House.

267
00:13:10.643 --> 00:13:11.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia <i>is </i>worthy.

268
00:13:12.163 --> 00:13:13.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course she is.

269
00:13:14.203 --> 00:13:16.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's an honorable woman
and a formidable warrior.

270
00:13:16.901 --> 00:13:18.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should say <i>that </i>to Sirella.

271
00:13:20.377 --> 00:13:21.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not such a good idea.

272
00:13:22.080 --> 00:13:23.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't want her to think

273
00:13:23.721 --> 00:13:26.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I'm interfering
in her domain.

274
00:13:28.338 --> 00:13:29.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps I should
speak with her.

275
00:13:30.537 --> 00:13:32.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Coming from me, it would
not seem like a challenge

276
00:13:32.999 --> 00:13:33.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to her authority.

277
00:13:34.016 --> 00:13:35.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

278
00:13:37.455 --> 00:13:38.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

279
00:13:39.654 --> 00:13:41.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, um...

280
00:13:41.334 --> 00:13:43.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the truth is...

281
00:13:44.473 --> 00:13:46.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she doesn't like you
that much either.

282
00:13:46.633 --> 00:13:48.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me.

283
00:13:48.674 --> 00:13:50.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't let that
bother you.

284
00:13:50.325 --> 00:13:52.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had every right
to bring you into the family

285
00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:54.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and she's accepted the fact

286
00:13:54.691 --> 00:13:56.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that there's <i>nothing</i>
she can do about it.

287
00:13:57.429 --> 00:13:58.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How comforting.

288
00:14:00.068 --> 00:14:00.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckles </i>)

289
00:14:01.028 --> 00:14:04.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

290
00:14:04.107 --> 00:14:07.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they say that
you have no sense of humor.

291
00:14:07.786 --> 00:14:10.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

292
00:14:24.341 --> 00:14:26.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Phew. I could do
without the heat.

293
00:14:26.740 --> 00:14:29.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't, uh, say much
for the decor either.

294
00:14:29.834 --> 00:14:31.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, it can't be
<i>all </i>fun and games.

295
00:14:32.002 --> 00:14:34.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure there has to be
some sort of ritual

296
00:14:34.340 --> 00:14:36.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we have to go through
before the party begins.

297
00:14:37.339 --> 00:14:40.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There <i>is </i>going to be
a party, isn't there?

298
00:14:40.716 --> 00:14:41.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're asking me?

299
00:14:42.513 --> 00:14:44.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can barely say
my name in Klingon.

300
00:14:44.807 --> 00:14:46.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
Prepare yourselves, my friends

301
00:14:47.633 --> 00:14:49.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for a journey
you won't soon forget.

302
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These...

303
00:14:56.711 --> 00:14:58.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
are <i>Ma'Stakas.</i>

304
00:14:58.190 --> 00:14:59.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What, uh, what do
we do with them?

305
00:15:00.030 --> 00:15:02.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At the conclusion
of the wedding ceremony

306
00:15:02.850 --> 00:15:04.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you will use them
to attack Worf and Dax.

307
00:15:05.209 --> 00:15:06.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously.
Don't you know anything?

308
00:15:07.048 --> 00:15:08.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The tradition dates back

309
00:15:08.149 --> 00:15:09.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the wedding
of Kahless and Lukara

310
00:15:09.527 --> 00:15:11.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who were nearly killed
by Molor's troops

311
00:15:11.407 --> 00:15:12.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
moments after they were
married.

312
00:15:13.806 --> 00:15:14.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Until the ceremony,

313
00:15:15.288 --> 00:15:16.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you should keep these with you
at all times.

314
00:15:16.647 --> 00:15:17.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
I trust

315
00:15:17.765 --> 00:15:19.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this combat is non-lethal.

316
00:15:20.244 --> 00:15:22.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is a symbolic
attack only.

317
00:15:22.724 --> 00:15:23.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

318
00:15:25.334 --> 00:15:26.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That food is not
to be eaten.

319
00:15:28.972 --> 00:15:30.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what is it for?

320
00:15:30.292 --> 00:15:33.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is there to tempt us
to break our fast.

321
00:15:33.171 --> 00:15:34.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fast?

322
00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:36.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There are six trials

323
00:15:36.341 --> 00:15:38.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we must face
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

324
00:15:38.337 --> 00:15:40.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the first--
deprivation.

325
00:15:41.298 --> 00:15:43.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We now begin a fast
that will continue

326
00:15:43.279 --> 00:15:44.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until the day of the wedding.

327
00:15:44.879 --> 00:15:46.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, th-that's
four days away.

328
00:15:46.619 --> 00:15:48.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
It is a short time,

329
00:15:48.018 --> 00:15:49.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know, but we must
make the best of it.

330
00:15:50.756 --> 00:15:53.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are
the other five trials?

331
00:15:53.094 --> 00:15:55.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Blood, pain, sacrifice,
anguish...

332
00:15:56.587 --> 00:15:57.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and death.

333
00:15:57.413 --> 00:15:59.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sounds like marriage,
all right.

334
00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:00.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How would you know?

335
00:16:00.577 --> 00:16:01.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is time to begin.

336
00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:09.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Need more flowers on the banister.

337
00:16:09.169 --> 00:16:10.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MALE: We're ready
with the banner, boss.

338
00:16:10.769 --> 00:16:11.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>whistles </i>)

339
00:16:11.969 --> 00:16:13.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Raise it.

340
00:16:13.089 --> 00:16:14.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're up early.

341
00:16:15.128 --> 00:16:16.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought writers
slept late.

342
00:16:16.447 --> 00:16:17.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not always.

343
00:16:17.806 --> 00:16:18.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I sold my first
book today.

344
00:16:19.445 --> 00:16:22.084 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? How much
did you get for it?

345
00:16:22.146 --> 00:16:23.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's just a
figure of speech.

346
00:16:23.886 --> 00:16:25.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Federation
News Service

347
00:16:25.087 --> 00:16:26.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is going to publish
a book of my stories

348
00:16:26.517 --> 00:16:27.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about life on the station
under Dominion rule.

349
00:16:27.796 --> 00:16:29.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they're not
paying you?

350
00:16:29.999 --> 00:16:30.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

351
00:16:30.636 --> 00:16:32.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, then you have
my sympathies

352
00:16:32.275 --> 00:16:33.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the first round
of drinks is on the house.

353
00:16:34.442 --> 00:16:34.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

354
00:16:35.882 --> 00:16:38.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. It's a figure
of speech.

355
00:16:38.741 --> 00:16:40.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I want to tell
my dad about the book.

356
00:16:40.341 --> 00:16:41.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is he still in
the holosuite?

357
00:16:42.639 --> 00:16:44.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, yeah.
They're still up there.

358
00:16:44.539 --> 00:16:46.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are they doing?

359
00:16:46.419 --> 00:16:49.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a Klingon
bachelor party.

360
00:16:51.097 --> 00:16:52.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're a writer.

361
00:16:52.217 --> 00:16:53.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Use your imagination.

362
00:16:56.775 --> 00:16:59.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR:
Alexander.

363
00:16:59.855 --> 00:17:01.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandma?

364
00:17:02.497 --> 00:17:03.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Guess again.

365
00:17:06.392 --> 00:17:07.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're still on the...?

366
00:17:07.713 --> 00:17:10.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The road to <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
day 500.

367
00:17:12.151 --> 00:17:13.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we should
turn down the heat

368
00:17:14.191 --> 00:17:16.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you know, for
Alexander's sake.

369
00:17:16.029 --> 00:17:18.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, it's okay.
I, uh...

370
00:17:18.149 --> 00:17:19.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just need some water.

371
00:17:20.489 --> 00:17:22.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you don't want
to push yourself too hard.

372
00:17:23.017 --> 00:17:25.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, turning down the heat
might be a good idea.

373
00:17:26.845 --> 00:17:28.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The whole point
is to push yourself

374
00:17:28.965 --> 00:17:31.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the limits
of your endurance.

375
00:17:33.084 --> 00:17:34.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>panting </i>)

376
00:17:37.483 --> 00:17:37.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will.

377
00:17:39.062 --> 00:17:41.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to travel
the entire path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

378
00:17:42.202 --> 00:17:43.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stoke the fire again!

379
00:17:43.403 --> 00:17:44.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you wish.

380
00:17:46.113 --> 00:17:50.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course, we cannot expect
you non-Klingons to...

381
00:17:51.479 --> 00:17:53.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have the same stamina
as we do.

382
00:17:53.738 --> 00:17:56.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you wish to quit,
no one will think

383
00:17:56.219 --> 00:17:56.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
any less of you.

384
00:17:57.637 --> 00:17:59.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who said anything
about quitting?

385
00:17:59.277 --> 00:18:01.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not me.

386
00:18:01.116 --> 00:18:03.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like the heat.

387
00:18:03.276 --> 00:18:05.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's the spirit.

388
00:18:06.994 --> 00:18:09.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Kaaa vek ko lee ko </i>♪

389
00:18:09.154 --> 00:18:11.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>eh to che maH lo </i>♪

390
00:18:11.833 --> 00:18:16.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
♪ <i>TaH oo-wah kaH esh to</i>
<i>pah deH ah reee! </i>♪

391
00:18:16.511 --> 00:18:19.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

392
00:18:19.191 --> 00:18:21.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

393
00:18:21.510 --> 00:18:23.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh tomaH! </i>♪

394
00:18:23.990 --> 00:18:25.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Al'qoch</i>

395
00:18:25.308 --> 00:18:26.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>mensaH</i>

396
00:18:26.468 --> 00:18:27.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>t'lang</i>

397
00:18:27.428 --> 00:18:28.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>cho.</i>

398
00:18:31.867 --> 00:18:33.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Again.

399
00:18:34.226 --> 00:18:36.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've done it
three times already.

400
00:18:36.466 --> 00:18:38.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You continue
to rush through the ceremony,

401
00:18:39.245 --> 00:18:41.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
your body
position is poor,

402
00:18:41.804 --> 00:18:43.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the placement
of the braziers

403
00:18:43.545 --> 00:18:45.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on their pedestals
is sloppy.

404
00:18:49.762 --> 00:18:51.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how heavy
those things are?

405
00:18:52.386 --> 00:18:54.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman
would not complain.

406
00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:56.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You wouldn't make
a Klingon woman

407
00:18:56.701 --> 00:18:57.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
do it three times in a row.

408
00:18:57.860 --> 00:18:59.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have to.

409
00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:01.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She'd have done it correctly
the first time.

410
00:19:05.277 --> 00:19:06.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
End this now, Jadzia.

411
00:19:07.476 --> 00:19:09.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go back to your own people.

412
00:19:09.715 --> 00:19:11.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They will tolerate
your weaknesses

413
00:19:11.816 --> 00:19:14.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and your failings
in a way that a Klingon family

414
00:19:14.657 --> 00:19:15.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never will.

415
00:19:16.293 --> 00:19:19.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In our House, you would
always be an alien--

416
00:19:19.913 --> 00:19:21.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
an outsider.

417
00:19:21.592 --> 00:19:23.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At best, you'd be
an object of pity

418
00:19:23.869 --> 00:19:25.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you'd never
be accepted

419
00:19:25.771 --> 00:19:26.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never an equal

420
00:19:27.250 --> 00:19:30.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because you can never
truly be one of us.

421
00:19:37.247 --> 00:19:39.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma tlang'goS ak-bay</i>

422
00:19:39.927 --> 00:19:43.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hava'dak croosh tovaH</i>

423
00:19:43.685 --> 00:19:45.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

424
00:19:45.885 --> 00:19:47.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

425
00:19:47.844 --> 00:19:50.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless.</i>

426
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:02.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the Second Dynasty ended
when General K'Trelan

427
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:03.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
assassinated Emperor Reclaw.

428
00:20:03.659 --> 00:20:06.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the next ten years,
the Empire was ruled

429
00:20:06.560 --> 00:20:08.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
by a Council elected
by the people.

430
00:20:08.897 --> 00:20:10.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Modern-day
Klingon historians

431
00:20:10.798 --> 00:20:12.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
refer to this
as "The Dark Time."

432
00:20:13.516 --> 00:20:17.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's interesting to note
that this first and only

433
00:20:17.498 --> 00:20:19.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
experiment
in Klingon democracy

434
00:20:19.635 --> 00:20:21.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
actually produced
several reforms...

435
00:20:21.533 --> 00:20:23.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are straying from the saga.

436
00:20:23.452 --> 00:20:24.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Am I?

437
00:20:26.171 --> 00:20:29.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your task is to recite
the complete chronicle

438
00:20:29.770 --> 00:20:31.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the women in my family.

439
00:20:32.871 --> 00:20:33.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just thought I'd give you

440
00:20:33.772 --> 00:20:36.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a broader historical perspective
along the way.

441
00:20:36.570 --> 00:20:38.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am familiar
with Klingon history.

442
00:20:40.109 --> 00:20:44.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, return to the story
of my 23rd maternal grandmother

443
00:20:45.347 --> 00:20:48.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shenara,
daughter of Emperor Reclaw

444
00:20:48.812 --> 00:20:49.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Second Dynasty.

445
00:20:49.946 --> 00:20:52.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, that's where we run
into a little bit of a problem.

446
00:20:53.244 --> 00:20:54.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see, I did some research

447
00:20:55.083 --> 00:20:57.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and when Emperor Reclaw
was killed,

448
00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:59.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
all of the members
of the Imperial Family

449
00:20:59.744 --> 00:21:01.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were put to death,
including Shenara.

450
00:21:02.741 --> 00:21:05.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
